==English==

===Noun===
'''establishment''' ('''establishments''')
#the act of [[establish]]ing
#:''Since their '''establishment''' of the company in 1984, they have grown into a global business.''
<!--is this really a different definition from 1?-->
#the act of being [[establish]]ed
#:''The firm celebrated twenty years since their '''establishment''' by updating their look.''
#the place in which a business is located or the business itself 
#:''Pedro's is a fine '''establishment''' serving a variety of delicious food.''
#{{slang}} '''the establishment''':  the ruling class or authority group in a society; esepecially, an [[entrenched]] authority dedicated to preserving the [[status quo]].
#:''It's often necessary to question '''the establishment''' to get things done.''  

